result.execSummary:
Charge(s) in this case were read in to this or other case(s). A "read in" charge is a charge that is dismissed as part of a plea agreement, however:

  • The defendant agrees to have the court consider the charge(s) when sentencing for another crime, under Wis. Stats. 973.20(1g)(b); and
  • The defendant cannot be prosecuted for these charge(s) in the future.

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. records.addlTxt:
Attorney Pangburns motion to withdraw as counsel.
The defendant requests that his attorney put in bail reduction and he refused to do so, the defendant therefore wishes for him to withdraw.
The court advises that Attorneys have a duty to their clients and the court, and that the defendant does not get to choose his attorney. If the defendant keeps firing attorneys it may result in the court deeming that he is waiving his right to attorney.
The court finds based upon colloquy with the defendant and the attorney it would be appropriate for the motion to be granted.
The court will sign order. 
The bail modification motion will be set for July 24, 2018 at 10:30 a.m.

The matter was set for a motion hearing today.
The court met with the parties in chambers prior to the case being called.  Attorney Falk subpoenaed the co-defendant, Shaika Oliver, for the hearing today and also notified Attorney Belville of doing so.  The Court questioned the co-defendants 5th amendment rights since the scope of the cross examination will not be limited to direct examination.  Based on this information, Attorney Belville told Ms. Oliver not to testify in this matter.
At this time, Attorney Falk withdraws the motion.  The Court deems the motion withdrawn.
